{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10063,"record_hash":"sha256:6a0827b7429e1a354ec0b7b6155042f622aa4211a7b5acb7aea70ed7397c761d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:18.865Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 550fe6\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1370\nOutput:\n\n## Minimal Tool Draft\n\nThe minimal agent-facing surface should be three read tools:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions [branch [<branch>] | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> [--limit N]\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> [--from start|end|<index>] [--limit N]\n```\n\nThis is enough for an agent to:\n\n1. discover prior sessions\n2. orient itself in the session and turn structure\n3. read bounded transcript records only where needed\n\nThere should not be a first-class `handoff` command. Handoff is the workflow the\nagent performs with these tools.\n\nIf `branch` is provided without a branch name, it should mean the current branch.\nThat keeps the common prompt easy:\n\n```text\nCheck whether there are prior agent sessions related to this branch and catch up.\n```\n\nThe CLI can keep storage terms like `session_key` and `turn_key` internally, but\nhuman-facing help should prefer `session id` and `turn id`. \"Key\" reads like an\nimplementation detail.\n\n### `sessions`\n\nPurpose: answer \"what sessions should I inspect?\"\n\nTargeted form:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions branch agentlog-turn-storage\n```\n\nUntargeted form:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions --limit 10\n```\n\nThe targeted form returns sessions related to a branch, review, or change. The\nuntargeted form returns recent project sessions. Both should return compact\norientation data.\n\nJSON should include:\n\n- requested target, if any\n- `session_key`\n- `updated_at`\n- `started_at`, if known\n- `turn_count`\n- `record_count`\n- `related_turn_keys`, only for targeted lookup\n- match evidence, not confidence:\n  - `matched_by`, for example `branch_observed`, `review_observed`,\n    `change_observed`, or `explicit_reference`\n  - `matched_turn_keys`\n  - other observed branch/review/change keys, when present\n- source metadata: agents, providers, models, tool versions\n- latest turn key and latest capture timestamp\n- latest user/assist\n[TRUNCATED]\n\n- `turn_key`\n- turn metadata\n- ordered transcript records\n- record index/range metadata\n- `next` and `previous` cursors or offsets when more records are available\n\nThe command must be bounded by default. Backfilled turns can contain thousands\nof records, so `records` should never accidentally dump a whole historical\nsession because one turn was large. If the agent needs more, it can read the\nnext or previous range.\n\n`--from end` should be the default. For handoff, the latest records in a huge\nbackfill are usually more useful than the oldest records. The oldest records can\nstill matter for the original task prompt, so `--from start` should remain\navailable.\n\nEven when reading from `end`, return records in natural transcript order within\nthe selected window. For example, \"last 100 records\" should render oldest to\nnewest across those 100 records.\n\nResponses should include stable range metadata:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"range\": {\n    \"start_index\": 4900,\n    \"end_index\": 4999,\n    \"total_records\": 5000,\n    \"has_more_before\": true,\n    \"has_more_after\": false,\n    \"previous_from\": 4800,\n    \"next_from\": null\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe first version should not add record-kind filtering. Return ordered records\nwith clear `kind`, `role`, `tool_name`, and redacted text fields. The consuming\nagent can decide to skim tool calls, skip noisy tool results, or read them when\ntests/errors/commands matter.\n\nRecord-kind, path, command, or error filtering can come later if real catch-up\nsessions prove that raw bounded windows are still too noisy.\n\n## Simulation Findings\n\nSix agent-consumer simulations mostly agreed on the shape:\n\n- keep the command set small\n- make the first response a triage surface, not just opaque ids\n- default to recent/tail-oriented reads for catch-up\n- keep raw ordered records as truth\n- expose ambiguity instead of product-y confidence scores\n\nThe main pressure points were:\n\n- `sessions` must explain why each session matched the requested target\n- `timeline` must include enough previews and metadata to choose turns without\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:18.865Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}